resumen:
Pl√°sticos Industriales de Tampico, S.A. de C.V. una compa√±√≠a a su servicio desde 1965 pionera en el desarrollo de la industria del pl√°stico reforzado. Introdujo en M√©xico la primera tecnolog√≠a de Filament-wound mediante una franquicia de Justin Enterprises Inc. (posteriormente Tankinetics Inc.), empresa de EUA l√≠der en el mercado mundial de tanques de pl√°stico reforzado.

En 1980 adquiri√≥ tecnolog√≠a de Casals Cardona Ind, empresa europea que cuenta con t√©cnicas nuevas en el uso de termopl√°sticos (PVC, PE, PVDF y PP) que son utilizables en combinaci√≥n (Dual-Laminate) con el pl√°stico reforzado tradicional, logrando as√≠ ampliar la gama de aplicaciones contra la corrosi√≥n. PITSA es una compa√±√≠a l√≠der en el dise√±o y fabricaci√≥n de equipo de pl√°stico reforzado, empleando el proceso de Filament-Wound para la construcci√≥n de tanques, tuber√≠as y ductos, as√≠ como en el uso de moldeo manual (Hand Lay Up) para la manufactura de ventiladores, campanas, chimeneas, v√°lvulas y rejillas.

Pl√°sticos Industriales de Tampico, S.A. de C.V. commercially introduced original FRP technology in 1965. We currently design and manufacture FRP tanks, pipe, and duct systems, employing either hand lay-up, the spray-up, and the filament winding process.

PITSA grating is compression molded for superior strength and durability. Continuous research with quality partners such as Ashland, AOC, Owens Corning and others, as well as new product development, evolved our dual laminate expertise with PVC, Kynar, and Polypropylene to include an even broader range of options for corrosive applications. resumen:
ONE PARTNER. WORLDWIDE SUPPORT.

With more specialists in more locations around the globe, LOC Group balances exceptional responsiveness with on-the-ground expertise where it is needed. Since 1979, we have been tackling the most urgent and complex challenges across the shipping, renewables, oil & gas and marine assurance and risk sectors. This is the experience we draw on to bring you a fast and efficient response, whatever the situation. As an independent consultancy you can rely on our integrity and you can be assured that we will deliver the best possible result on your behalf.

Our people are the backbone of our business. We have over 400 professionally qualified full-time employees and dedicated contract personnel from a wide variety of backgrounds ‚Äì including twenty nationalities and at least twelve languages. Collectively our people offer a diverse range of technical skills and expertise, as well as an understanding of the cultures, customs and sensitivities of the countries in which we operate.

resumen:

resumen:
Grupo Marpa se va conformando gracias a la visi√≥n e √≠mpetu de Don Jes√∫s Mart√≠nez Cabeza de Vaca, quien en 1976 decide incursionar en forma particular en los negocios, estableciendo en Papantla, Veracruz, una gasolinera con servicio de lavado, engrasado, ventas de llantas y refacciones. Dicha empresa a postre ya no existe, sin embargo le proporciono los conocimientos e impulso necesarios para incursionar en mercados m√°s amplios.

En la medida que el tiempo a transcurrido se han ido agregando a la direcci√≥n de las empresas diversos miembros de la familia de Don Jes√∫s, en particular sus hijos,quienes junto sus colaboradores han engrandecido y diversificado los ramos comerciales a los que se dedica el Grupo Marpa. Es a ra√≠z de esta misma diversidad de negocios que actualmente la direcci√≥n operativa del grupo es llevada a cabo por dos de sus hijos, encarg√°ndose cada uno de las empresas de cierto ramo comercial en particular. Siendo este un grupo empresarial b√°sicamente familiar con contadas inclusiones de socios, la estructura administrativa se conforma por dos corporativos con cedes en la Cd de M√©xico y Pachuca, integrados por los due√±os y su correspondiente equipo de colaboradores, los cuales tienen como misi√≥n primordial el mantener informada a la direcci√≥n sobre el desempe√±o de las diversas empresas, as√≠ como el de supervisar y capacitar al personal.

Las empresas del Grupo Marpa son todas unidades aut√≥nomas de producci√≥n, las cuales cuentan con la suficiente infraestructura humana y material para operar de manera independiente.

Actualmente los principales giros comerciales a los que se dedica el Grupo Marpa son:

Deportes - F√∫tbol de Primera Divisi√≥n.

resumen:
Since 1997, CRM Synergies has been a leading manufacturer of solder alloys for the electronic industry. Our worldwide renowned brand offers a wide range of services to meet the needs of customers in the electronic industry.

Headquartered in Spain, CRM Synergies has offices and factories in Brazil, Mexico, USA, Hungary, France, Tunisia, and Poland.

Who is CRM Synergies?

‚û§ Tin Alloy Manufacturing:
- CRM supplies efficient and high-quality products for various soldering processes.
- We manufacture metal alloys and fluxes in our own facilities, which are distributed worldwide.
- As one of the most important manufacturers of Tin Alloys in Europe, we cater to the American market from our facilities in Brazil and serve Mexico as well.

‚û§ Worldwide Tin Solder Reclaim:
- CRM has developed special processes to recycle all types of solder paste waste.
- We recycle waste materials such as Dross, Ashes, Powder, Sludge, Metal, regardless of their format.

‚û§ Global Electronic Specialist in Spare Parts and Consumables:
- CRM is a leading global specialist in providing spare parts and consumables for SMT and THT assembly lines of major manufacturers.
- Our product range includes feeders, feeder spare parts, splicing products, splicing tapes, tape connectors, splice clips, splice tools, nozzles, filters, and maintenance spare parts.

Our Advantages:
- Cost reduction up to 60%.
- High quality.
- Local support and service.
- Warranty coverage.

CRM Synergies guarantees quick and efficient service through our distributor network, which covers all five continents.

Contact Us:

resumen:
Welcome to ROCKA, your trusted partner in global manufacturing and distribution solutions. We specialize in enhancing your supply chain by prioritizing value through:
Competitive Pricing: At ROCKA, we understand the importance of cost competitiveness in today's global marketplace. Our team is dedicated to developing and maintaining competitive pricing strategies to ensure you receive optimal value for your investments.
Inventory Management: Precision in inventory management is the cornerstone of efficient operations. We excel in optimizing inventory levels, minimizing carrying costs, and ensuring that you have the right products at the right time to meet market demands.
On-Time Deliveries: Time is money, and at ROCKA, we value both. Our commitment to punctual deliveries is unwavering. Count on us to meet your deadlines, providing reliability and consistency in supply chain execution.
Technical Support: Navigating the complexities of manufacturing and distribution often requires technical expertise. Our experienced team is here to offer comprehensive technical support, ensuring smooth operations and addressing any challenges that may arise.
Global Reach, Local Presence: With many years of combined experience, ROCKA has established itself as a global player with a national presence. We offer a spectrum of services, including warehousing, cutting-edge technologies, shipping solutions, and technical expertise tailored to the unique needs of the electronic and mechanical industries.
Cost-Effective Solutions: At ROCKA, our commitment extends beyond mere distribution. We pride ourselves on consistently providing cost-effective solutions that empower our customers to overcome challenges and gain a competitive edge in the market.
Whether you're seeking reliable warehousing, innovative technologies, or strategic shipping solutions, ROCKA is poised to be your partner in success.

resumen:
Precision Group is an industry leading designer and manufacturer of both injection-molded plastics and tooling across the medical, automotive, electronics, and consumer markets.  As an ISO9001:2008 certified facility, Precision Mold and Tool is committed to quality throughout the design and manufacturing process.

resumen:
QTEK Manufacturing Ltd. is a leading global manufacturer of SMT and critical cleaning consumables for electronics manufacturing and associated industries. With headquarters in Galway, Ireland, QTEK also hosts a manufacturing site in Guadalajara, Mexico. Over the last 30 years QTEK has established an extensive network of international distributors. QTEK only works with the most reputable and dedicated representatives in each territory to ensure QTEK products receive the necessary sales support around the globe

Rigorous quality control procedures ensure the consistent high standard of quality and reliability that are required for high-end electronics manufacturing.

At QTEK, we strive to become synonymous with excellence and are committed to providing the highest quality products possible, at a competitive price. With a dedicated research and development team, QTEK merges technological advances with our own in-depth product knowledge, to provide products best suited to our customers needs. Our commitment to customer service is second to none; we aim to support our customers and distribution partners with superior quality products, value and dedicated sales support.

nombre: Bryan, Gonzalez Vargas & Gonzalez Baz, S.C.
resumen: The firm has its origins in 1945 with the merger of a banking and corporate practice. It was founded by Chilton Bryan and Aureliano Gonzalez Vargas in Mexico City and relocated its offices to Ciudad Juarez, Chihuahua that same year. The dynamic evolution of Mexican economic policy over the years has meant that effective legal counsel be characterized by scope and depth of experience as well as flexibility in responding to change as Mexico continues on the path toward joining the ranks of the industrialized countries of the world. Since the decade of the 1960's the Firm has played a prominent role in the formulation and implementation of Mexican development policy, to include the northern border economic expansion programs such as the Maquiladora (‚ÄúIn-Bond") Program as well as participation in private debt restructuring and corporate planning projects necessitated by economic conditions in Mexico during the 1980's. Today, Bryan, Gonzalez Vargas & Gonzalez Baz, S.C., is actively involved in the economic liberalization policies that are propelling Mexico into the mainstream of the world economy. Such movement has been further stimulated by the North American Free Trade Agreement, the United States and Canada. It is note worthy to mention that the Firm provided guidance to one of the governments based on its years of experience representing the business interests of international clients in Mexico.

resumen:
Ectipsa USA, LLC specializes in the manufacture and repair of equipment for the oil & gas industry, offering variety of repair services and products such as valves, spools, flanges, fittings, BOP components, and choke manifolds.

Ectipsa USA, LLC have been manufacturing replacement parts for blowout preventers as well as repairing them for over 14 years in Mexico. We have also done many shear bonnet conversions with boosters for Cameron, Hydril, Shaffer, and Chinese blowout preventers. Ectipsa USA, LLC also manufactures and repairs all types of choke and kill manifolds. 

We have a Rental Division and a Flow Line Division, where we carry a large number of plug valve manifolds, crossovers, pup joints, safety valves, integral fittings, as well as all sorts of Instrumentation for the gas meter and testing Industry.

Third party inspections can be offered by companies such as ABS or DNV when the customer requires. All repairs are accompanied with complete repair documentation, test charts, dimensional and visual inspection certificates.

resumen: Bettcher Manufacturing is in the business of producing quality stampings. Established in 1894, Bettcher has a long history of manufacturing metal components. Headquartered in McAllen, Texas, with a manufacturing facility in Reynosa, Mexico, they are equipped to handle products ranging from small, very intricate parts to large gage, deep drawn housings for nearly any type of industry. The company‚Äôs equipment is new, modern and capable of producing precision products. Bettcher encompasses a variety of presses, from 60 to 900 tons, and has the technology for processing progressive, line and transfer tooling. As an engineering focused company, Bettcher offers their expertise while products are still on the drawing board as well as assisting in cost reduction efforts through design improvements. Learn more about Bettcher Manufacturing at www.bettcherllc.com.

resumen:
Haemotronic was founded in 1979 in Mirandola (Italy) by the Ravizza Family to support family pharma businesses with manufacturing of single-use medical devices. We are now a leading provider of medical disposables. 

We develop, design and manufacture a wide range of medical products for both medical and pharmaceutical industry: we use high quality materials (including DEHP FREE) and modern technologies to transform them into tubes, OEM components, EVA Bags and PVC-free Bags. Our manufacturing capabilities and areas of expertise include Injection Molding, Extrusion, Thermal and RF welding, Heat sealing, UV curing, EtO, Gamma and Steam sterilization processes.

Today Haemotronic has its main HQ and main production plants in Mirandola and Carbonara, Italy and one plant in Reynosa, Mexico, counting 600+ employees in total. We have developed an international presence by distributing our products in Latin America and by creating strong business relationships in the Middle East and in the Far East.

We constantly invest in Research and Development to meet the highest standards. 
We can fully customize products from start to finish to best meet your requirements. 

Check out our website to find out more!

Find out why Hot-Hed¬Æ International's biggest Clients have continued to choose our Oilfield Service Company to provide them with the Petroleum Industry Products and Oilfield Services they need for nearly 50 years. Hot-Hed¬Æ employs only first-class Welders, Technicians & Petroleum Engineers who are fully certified & who specialize in their fields. In addition, all of Hot-Hed¬Æ's team members undergo a regular cycle of rigorous safety orientation, training & evaluation programs from the time of initial hire throughout their career with Hot-Hed¬Æ, ensuring that even our biggest Oil & Gas Industry Clients receive the quality Services & Products they demand. With Hot-Hed¬Æ's highly experienced, skilled crews on the job, your Company can be assured of quality workmanship & superior results every time.

The key to Hot-Hed¬Æ‚Äôs continual success & growth is our constant development of new, innovative oil & gas industry products & services & the ongoing development of our tagline - "JUST A BETTER WAY TO DO THINGS". resumen:
At Alliance Specialized Systems, we are leaders in fire protection and security solutions, with over 20 years of experience and a team of more than 300 highly trained professionals. With one office in Texas and seven in Mexico, we provide nationwide coverage across Mexico and serve key regions in the US, ensuring a fast and efficient response for our clients.

We specialize in the design, supply, installation, and ITM of fire protection systems, ensuring compliance with NFPA, FM Global, VdS, and local regulations. Our operations are backed by ISO 9001 (Quality), 45001 (Safety), and 37001 (Anti-Bribery) certifications, guaranteeing the highest standards in every project.

As a company committed to excellence and innovation, we are active members of NFSA and SFPE, as well as founding members of AMRACI (Mexican Association of Fire Sprinklers), CONAPCI (National Fire Protection Council), and LATAM PCI (Latin American Fire Protection Network).

Our team holds the highest NICET Certifications, Levels IV in Fire Sprinklers, Special Hazards, and Alarm & Detection, ensuring compliance with the highest industry standards. In Mexico, we have the largest number of engineers certified in CETRACI, CEDACI, and CEMACI, reinforcing our leadership and expertise.

We provide tailored solutions for every client and risk type. Some of our key services include:
 ‚Ä¢ Fire sprinkler systems (wet, dry, pre-action, deluge)
 ‚Ä¢ Fire suppression for special hazards (gas, foam, water mist)
 ‚Ä¢ Fire alarm and detection systems
 ‚Ä¢ Fire pumps and water storage tanks
 ‚Ä¢ ITM (Inspection, testing, and maintenance)
 ‚Ä¢ Security systems: CCTV, access control, and BMS automation

With an experienced team, specialized certifications, and a strong commitment to quality, safety, and sustainability, we deliver reliable and cost-effective solutions that ensure protection, operational continuity, and regulatory compliance.

Contact us to learn how we can protect your facilities with industry-leading solutions.

resumen:
Custom Molded Sealing Product Solutions,

Founded in Milwaukee in 1858 and headquartered in Lake Geneva Wisconsin, Trostel is part of Park Ohio.  The company has a rich tradition of providing high performance seals, custom molded products and custom mixed compounds to both mobile and industrial markets.

Competency and capability
Trostel‚Äôs applications expertise, seal design experience and molding capability is supported by a strong competency in elastomeric polymer development. These align well with the needs of the design engineer.

We understand how each application‚Äôs environment acts on seal performance and durability. Whether it is fluid compatibility, a wide temperature range, abrasion or low torque we can provide the right material and component design to meet your application. Our strength is component integration where dimensional accuracy and bond integrity between the rubber and carrier are critical. We specialize in the latest rubber to metal adhesive systems. As a solutions provider we are comfortable with the design and molding of complex geometries.

The way we work
Trostel seeks to collaborate early in the design cycle so as to gain a solid understanding of the customers design goals and program milestones. We then work with the customer to specify the correct material and design to provide the optimum value in a sealing solution.  To verify the solution we perform application and endurance testing in our Technical Center.

resumen:
Legotec is an API Q1 manufacturer with over 30 years of combined experience in manufacturing and delivering high-quality oil field tools. We specialize in the fabrication of Downhole Drill Stem components, along with the threading and repair of API and Double Shoulder rotary connections in accordance with API Spec 7-1 requirements.

Our manufacturing criteria is focused in On-Time Production, API Q1 Standards, confidentiality and strict control of customers requirements. This way we guarantee our commitment and complete satisfaction to our customers.

nombre: ITW Air Flow Management North America
resumen:
Did you know that you are never a few steps away from something somewhere that ITW as a whole makes?

ITW Air Flow Management delivers differentiated value to the North American Automotive OEM (Original Equipment Manufacturer) by addressing industry trends of autonomous driving, display integration and customized environments.  We are a producer of interior components such as Pressure Relief Valves (PRVs) and Air Registers bringing in approximately $88M of revenue.

Our division has 3 locations and approximately 530+ employees in North America.  Our manufacturing locations are in Westminster, MA and Reynosa, Mexico.  In addition, our Sales, Engineering and Product Development team are located in Troy, MI.

resumen:
G-Box is one of North America's leading producers of corrugated and consumer packaging and recycling solutions. Strategically located in the US and Mexico (Dallas, Monterrey & Reynosa), G-box produces foldable packaging and micro-corrugated products such as; folding cartons, multi-packs, displays, blister cards, points of purchase and rigid & micro-corrugated boxes.

With a low-cost position in the marketplace, G-box commits every day to creating and delivering value with innovation that produces new product ideas, generates revenue gains, improves equipment effectiveness and increases the quality of our work force. A performance-based, data-driven culture also helps G-box continuously reduce costs and increase customer satisfaction.

resumen:
Impacte provides inventory management and warehouse services that solve the biggest inventory challenges.

A large amount of capital is tied up in inventory and for many companies that number approaches 50% of total assets. Inventory and warehouse problems pose a significant risk to the cost of these assets in non-core competency areas. The effect of these problems is lost revenue and reduced profit margins. These problems are universal and we solve them everyday.

Impacte's team provides warehouse and inventory management services using its unique and one-of-a-kind system that blends together all the elements of a warehouse to make a sound strategic solution.  Impacte works equally well whether the warehouse is at your facility or at an offsite location. 

Most companies do not measure their non-core competency areas like they do their core competency areas and warehouse's are non-core competency areas.   This results in lost profits!!!

By using impacte's one-of-a-kind system your company will receive the following benefits:

50% reduction in the cost of the mistakes being made in non-core competency areas such as a warehouse

Reduced inventory variances

Reduced obsolescence by tracking 

Reduced expedites

Reduced downtime on your production lines

Improved reporting providing real-time data

Reduced operating costs

Increased profits

Impacte can be up and running in under 30 days. But most importantly impacte saves you money while improving overall warehouse processes.  Call or email today for a free evaluation.

resumen:
In today‚Äôs disruptive world, you need more than a cargo agent.

Running a global supply chain is a complex, non-stop undertaking and, in the world of time-sensitive shipping, there is little margin for error. So, imagine having in your supply chain a strategic partner in logistics specialized in the singular task of getting things where they need to be, handling your programmed shipments with time-sensitive expertise, including when your cargo becomes urgent. That partner is Europartners Group.

Our own offices with teams strategically positioned around the globe are also connected to the best networks of agents in the Air, Ocean Ground Freight.

We work hard to make logistics simple and effective for you. Rely on high-coordination logistics, air freight and critical cargo specialists, with an experienced team in specialized industries.

We bring you and your clients closer, moving your products from and to wherever you need them. On time, with the full visibility that gives you peace of mind. This is what a smooth supply chain feels like.

Always fast, friendly and dedicated, our corporate culture led us to be a Top+ Company where everyone wants to work. 

That has enabled us to select the best professionals in several industries for the last 20 years and motivate them to walk hand in hand with you to get the best options in international freight services, tailored for your needs, with a great customer experience. 

Connect with us. We are Europartners Group.
Connecting minds to move the world.

resumen:
Welldex Logistics - A World of Solutions.

For 100 years we have made a more accessible world by developing and executing logistics solutions so that organizations around the world can open their doors to the global market safely and with a solid foundation.

We are known for our focus on our clients' success through a best-in-class customer experience.

At Welldex Logistics we are aligned to a culture focused on five values:
  - Exceptional Service
  - Integrity
  - Passion
  - Innovation
  - Resilience

Solutions:
  - Air, land, sea, multimodal & project cargo transportation
  - Customs and Regulatory Compliance

resumen:
4Front Engineered Solutions is a global leader in entrance solutions, providing one of the world‚Äôs most comprehensive lines of entrance automation products and warehouse solutions. With over 60 years of knowledge and expertise, 4Front is home to industry leading brands: Kelley, Serco, TKO Dock Doors, APS Resource, 4SIGHT, Epic Fans, Albany and Dynaco. 

As your complete partner in entrance automation systems, our brands Kelley, Serco and TKO Dock Doors provide dock equipment and warehouse solutions, 4SIGHT offers digital connectivity at yards and facilities, APS Resource supplies aftermarket needs, Epic Fans delivers energy efficient HVLS fans, and Albany and Dynaco manufacture high-performance doors. A great suite of products to fulfill and transform the quality and efficiency of facility operations worldwide. 

4Front designs, manufactures and installs entrance automation solutions through a network of highly dedicated and well trained distributors and installers in some 80 countries worldwide. Our goal is to supply the critical needs of customers across warehousing, manufacturing, retail and distribution centers with the superior quality of our products.
Following its acquisition in December 2012, 4Front Engineered Solutions was strategically placed into the ASSA ABLOY Entrance Systems division.

resumen:
TS Tech Group, founded in 1960, is a high-quality manufacturer and distributor of high-quality seats and interior products. 

TS Tech Americas, Inc. (www.tstech.com) is the regional corporate headquarters, research and development, and strategic center for 17 locations throughout USA, Canada, Mexico and Brazil.  These locations manufacture and sale automotive and powersports seats, interior parts and accessories.  

At TS Tech Americas, Inc., we are committed to building a workplace where associates feel valued and inspired to take pride in being part of the TS Tech team. Our focus is on delivering customer satisfaction, protecting the environment, and actively supporting local community initiatives and organizations.

TS Tech - Beyond Comfort

We have adopted the corporate message "Beyond Comfort." "Beyond Comfort" emphasizes our will to push past the present boundaries toward a higher level of comfort.

In addition to our pursuit of safety and environmental friendliness, the TS Tech Group actively pursues comfort in the products we make. Comfort is a diverse and profound concept that evolves without end over the course of time.

Comfort brings satisfaction, which leads to happiness‚Äîthis is the idea that must be at the core of everything that we do as members of the TS Tech Group. Don‚Äôt be tied to the status quo. Go beyond the here and now to innovate. Doing that will allow us to offer happiness to society.

Our motto ‚ÄúBeyond Comfort‚Äù is meant to capture our intent to challenge ourselves to venture toward a world not yet seen.

(www.tstech.co.jp)

resumen:
At MEBC, we pride ourselves on the standard of excellence we maintain in every service we provide.  Our customers, and their customers, are our #1 priority.  MEBC's promise is to deliver unchallenged safety, quality and commitment in everything we do. 

Our network of operations covers 16 airports in Mexico, serving commercial airlines, private operations and freighters.  We currently offer both above wing (e.g., customer service, ticketing) and below wing (e.g., baggage handling, cargo) services. 

With more than 20 years of uninterrupted experience, we are constantly seeking to improve our service by growing alongside our customers.  Over the last few years, we have won multiple awards for our performance, including best overall ground handler and best airport operations in Mexico.

resumen:
Headquartered in Fort Worth, Texas, with facilities in North America, Europe and Asia, KMG (NYSE: KMG) manufactures, formulates and globally distributes specialty chemicals for the Electronics, Industrial Wood Preservation and Industrial Lubricants markets. 

Electronic Chemicals
As the complexity of semiconductor silicon wafers continues to advance, so too must the purity of the process chemicals used in their manufacture. KMG is proud to be a leading supplier of high purity process chemicals for many of the world‚Äôs leading technology companies. Our chemicals are used primarily to etch and clean silicon wafers in the production of semiconductors.

We supply a variety of ultra-pure process chemicals, including various concentrations of etchants, solvents and specialty chemical blends. We are committed to maintaining the strictest purity levels throughout the packaging and delivery process and can ship our process chemical products in gallon containers, drums, totes and tank wagons.

Wood Treating Chemicals
KMG is the only manufacturer of pentachlorophenol (penta) for the industrial wood preservation market in North America. Penta is used to preserve and protect wooden utility poles and cross-arms. Treating wood with penta extends its useful life by decades in these industrial applications.

Industrial Lubricants
Through its subsidiaries, Val-Tex and Sealweld, KMG is a leading global provider of high-performance products and services for industrial valve and actuator maintenance. Our comprehensive product portfolio includes valve lubricants, cleaners and sealants, as well as related products such as fittings, adapters and application equipment. We also offer routine and emergency valve maintenance services and technician training for many of the world‚Äôs leading pipeline operators. We are dedicated to enabling safe and optimal valve operation while preventing costly, unscheduled downtime at customer facilities and pipelines.

resumen:
Atlantic Tool & Die, Global Engineers and manufacturers of metal stampings manufactured from progressive/transfer dies utilizing Minster presses from 60 to 1200 tons. ATD specializes in value-added assemblies utilizing robotic and manual welding, riveting, tapping and nut/bolt insertion within 6 world class manufacturing locations totaling over 500,000 square feet. ATD provides products in such industries as:

Automotive as direct to OEM and as a Tier 1 or 2 supplier
Home Appliance, direct and indirect
Off road personal vehicles, direct and indirect
Construction Industries
Commercial Power Solutions
Green Energy Solutions

ATD further provides specialized services for:
Value Added Engineering
Safety Restraint systems
Body in White Structures
Seating System Assemblies
Tubular Products
New Tool & Die Construction
New Inspection Gage Construction

Teamed with our design center in Costa Rica ATD can meet all your stamping, assembly, gage, fixture, simulation and tooling requirements. Call us for a quote today.

resumen:
Boxes.mx (Empaques Rio Grande), is a leading manufacturing company in the corrugated cardboard packaging industry with more than 35 years of experience. We began operations with the objective of supplying the Mexican export industry. Currently, we have seven manufacturing facilities with state-of-the-art machinery distributed in the northeast, center and bajio of Mexico, consolidating ourselves as a trusted partner for companies in the automotive, electronic, medical, and aerospace industries, among others. Our facilities cover a combined area of more than 635,000 ft2 that allow us, as a manufacturer, to have full control of your production, inventory and logistic services.
The company is proud of its commitment to sustainability, it also strives to ensure that its operations are socially responsible, to build trust with our customers by always acting with the best ethical practices. Likewise, treating our more than 600 employees and local communities with respect and fairness.
Our team of experts at Boxes.mx understand how changing and dynamic the demand of our customers is, which is why we have a great customer service team with 24/7 service, offering flexibility in our operations to resolve all types of changes in programming and emergencies.

resumen:
Geopulse Exploration Inc. is a publicly listed, fully reporting jr exploration & mining company. Symbol: GPLS

Geopulse Exploration management seeks to build it success on the continued evaluation and development of precious metals properties throughout North, Central and South America. Our focus is on undervalued and distressed mineral assets and/or newly discovered properties.

Buoyed by experienced management, the Company is confident in its ability to secure return on capital investment by incorporating properties which have previously recognized, indicated and or inferred mineral resources through both geographical and historical evaluations. Cautious due diligence and planned multi-phase exploration programs should enable the Company to provide a greater possibility of return on investment.

The Company has taken great care in providing strong shareholder support by securing Management which have both social and technical expertise within the boundaries of the countries which Geopulse is preparing to move forward. Management continues to work with several key strategic partners to formulate a strategic business plan, following the Geopulse vision so as to develop corporate assets through joint venture and / or other financially viable transactions.

resumen:
Hepeca Logistics , Inc. is a privately owned company founded in 1993 by its President A.A. Ing. Heberto Perez C. We provide cost-effective Logistical services ranging from consulting on establishing Maquila plants in Mexico, to the actual import/export operations to and from Mexico. We are highly specialized in Maquila (IMMEX) operations (temporary imports into Mexico to be transformed and exported to the US), but handle a considerable volume of definitive operations into Mexico as well. Our main office, Warehouses and Distribution Center  is located in Laredo, TX. (Northbound and Southbound Warehouses) and our Mexico Counterpart in Nuevo Laredo, Tamps., Mexico. 

Our services include Mexican and US Customs Brokerage, Distribution Services, Freight Forwarding, and Transportation.

resumen:
TS Tech Group, founded in 1960, is a high-quality manufacturer and distributor of high-quality seats and interior products. 

TS Tech Americas, Inc. (www.tstech.com) is the regional corporate headquarters, research and development, and strategic center for 17 locations throughout USA, Canada, Mexico and Brazil.  These locations manufacture and sale automotive and powersports seats, interior parts and accessories.  

At TS Tech Americas, Inc., we are committed to building a workplace where associates feel valued and inspired to take pride in being part of the TS Tech team. Our focus is on delivering customer satisfaction, protecting the environment, and actively supporting local community initiatives and organizations.

TS Tech - Beyond Comfort

We have adopted the corporate message "Beyond Comfort." "Beyond Comfort" emphasizes our will to push past the present boundaries toward a higher level of comfort.

In addition to our pursuit of safety and environmental friendliness, the TS Tech Group actively pursues comfort in the products we make. Comfort is a diverse and profound concept that evolves without end over the course of time.

Comfort brings satisfaction, which leads to happiness‚Äîthis is the idea that must be at the core of everything that we do as members of the TS Tech Group. Don‚Äôt be tied to the status quo. Go beyond the here and now to innovate. Doing that will allow us to offer happiness to society.

Our motto ‚ÄúBeyond Comfort‚Äù is meant to capture our intent to challenge ourselves to venture toward a world not yet seen.

(www.tstech.co.jp)

resumen:
At MEBC, we pride ourselves on the standard of excellence we maintain in every service we provide.  Our customers, and their customers, are our #1 priority.  MEBC's promise is to deliver unchallenged safety, quality and commitment in everything we do. 

Our network of operations covers 16 airports in Mexico, serving commercial airlines, private operations and freighters.  We currently offer both above wing (e.g., customer service, ticketing) and below wing (e.g., baggage handling, cargo) services. 

With more than 20 years of uninterrupted experience, we are constantly seeking to improve our service by growing alongside our customers.  Over the last few years, we have won multiple awards for our performance, including best overall ground handler and best airport operations in Mexico.

resumen:
In today‚Äôs disruptive world, you need more than a cargo agent.

Running a global supply chain is a complex, non-stop undertaking and, in the world of time-sensitive shipping, there is little margin for error. So, imagine having in your supply chain a strategic partner in logistics specialized in the singular task of getting things where they need to be, handling your programmed shipments with time-sensitive expertise, including when your cargo becomes urgent. That partner is Europartners Group.

Our own offices with teams strategically positioned around the globe are also connected to the best networks of agents in the Air, Ocean Ground Freight.

We work hard to make logistics simple and effective for you. Rely on high-coordination logistics, air freight and critical cargo specialists, with an experienced team in specialized industries.

We bring you and your clients closer, moving your products from and to wherever you need them. On time, with the full visibility that gives you peace of mind. This is what a smooth supply chain feels like.

Always fast, friendly and dedicated, our corporate culture led us to be a Top+ Company where everyone wants to work. 

That has enabled us to select the best professionals in several industries for the last 20 years and motivate them to walk hand in hand with you to get the best options in international freight services, tailored for your needs, with a great customer experience. 

Connect with us. We are Europartners Group.
Connecting minds to move the world.

resumen:
Boxes.mx (Empaques Rio Grande), is a leading manufacturing company in the corrugated cardboard packaging industry with more than 35 years of experience. We began operations with the objective of supplying the Mexican export industry. Currently, we have seven manufacturing facilities with state-of-the-art machinery distributed in the northeast, center and bajio of Mexico, consolidating ourselves as a trusted partner for companies in the automotive, electronic, medical, and aerospace industries, among others. Our facilities cover a combined area of more than 635,000 ft2 that allow us, as a manufacturer, to have full control of your production, inventory and logistic services.
The company is proud of its commitment to sustainability, it also strives to ensure that its operations are socially responsible, to build trust with our customers by always acting with the best ethical practices. Likewise, treating our more than 600 employees and local communities with respect and fairness.
Our team of experts at Boxes.mx understand how changing and dynamic the demand of our customers is, which is why we have a great customer service team with 24/7 service, offering flexibility in our operations to resolve all types of changes in programming and emergencies.

resumen:
TRANSPAC was established more than 45 years ago, created in 1975 with the purpose of providing personalized services for the maritime industry in Mexico within the globalized market of import and export, representing foreign companies, and providing a wide portfolio of operations throughout the Mexican territory.

We operate through two divisions in order to satisfy our customer‚Äôs needs: Shipping Agents and Port Services. With direct operations in all commercial ports this division is capable to provide all type of port and vessel operations, including but not limited to stowage and cargo handling, bulk, break bulk, iso-tank, dry, and reefer container management; also Ro-Ro, tourist and project cargo services. As shipping agents we drive commercial activities from our HQ located in Mexico City, where we have special focus on the customer satisfaction; our people will care about your business being dedicated on the details, with a wide sales and operational expertise, specialized advisory to guide your operations in Mexico and our well connected value chain of enterprises ready to boost your business growth while keeping efficient operations.  

TRANSPAC is an active member of BIMCO (Baltic and International Maritime Council) since 1976, as well as AMANAC (Mexican Ship Agents Association), proudly certified by FONASBA Quality Standard and they also granted our operations managers with the Agent Diploma.  During our long history we have been recognized as a company with deep knowledge within the industry, well respected by our competitors and highly appreciated by our customers.

resumen:
Our team of experts is dedicated to providing exceptional customer service and delivering innovative solutions for hotels, restaurants, retail chains, stadiums, golf courses, and spas.

We take great pride in being a globally recognized hospitality software development company and with a presence in 104 countries and serving more than 14,000 customers, we have earned the distinction of being Oracle Hospitality's largest partner on a global scale.

Since our establishment in 1990, our primary goal has been to empower our clients and help them build stronger, more efficient, and ultimately more successful businesses.

Our extensive portfolio of products and services, which includes pre-project analysis, hardware and software supply, strategic IT consulting, and round-the-clock technical support, has firmly established us as a trusted provider of IT solutions. We are committed to being proactive contributors to the industry and constantly striving to exceed our clients' expectations.

resumen:
INDELPRO is one of the companies of Alpek, the Petrochemical Group of Grupo Alfa, and is the only producer of polypropylene resins in Mexico. Alpek's partner in this company is LyondellBasell, a global leader in polyolefin technology and production.

INDELPRO began its operations in March 1992 and has since marketed its products under the brands Valtec, Profax, Axlene, and Sphertec; products developed under strict quality standards. Our plant is located in Altamira, Tamaulipas, where the port infrastructure facilitates the reception of raw materials and the supply of products to our customers. Our headquarters are located in the municipality of Garza Garc√≠a, N.L., and we have sales offices in Mexico City.

INDELPRO successfully markets its products throughout the USMCA area, as well as Central and South America. Currently, INDELPRO has two polypropylene production lines, which provide us with the capacity to produce 690,000 tons annually.

resumen:
Alphagary, an Orbia business, is pioneering innovation solutions to advance life around the world.  Orbia‚Äôs Polymer Solutions business Alphagary is a global leader in the design and manufacture of specialty polymer compounds and additives for polyvinyl chloride compounds including stabilizers, plasticizers and colorants. 

Compounds are formulated from a variety of polymers including polyvinyl chloride (PVC), polyolefin (PO), thermoplastic polyurethane (TPU), and thermoplastic elastomer (TPE). With over 60 years of experience, Alphagary has earned its reputation for providing innovative, functional, durable solutions to a broad marketplace. 

Alphagary is committed to sustainability, offering products formulated with bio-based content and recycled content and active participation in initiatives that promote a circular economy. Its compounds are trusted for a wide range of applications from communications and power cables to various building and industrial products, automotive interior parts, a wide variety of consumer goods including food-contact applications and healthcare products. 

Alphagary offers standard and custom formulations to meet market-specific requirements and end users‚Äô needs and is committed to health and safety best practices by maintaining ISO 9001, ISO 14001 and OHS ISO 45001 certifications. Alphagary has 1,000 employees across nine facilities across the U.S., UK, Mexico, Colombia and India, serving 80 countries through a global sales and distribution network.

resumen: Founded in 1983 by principal shareholder William I. Koch, Oxbow is one of the world's largest recyclers of refinery and natural gas coproducts. Oxbow is headquartered in West Palm Beach, Florida with approximately 950 employees operating from more than 30 locations in 14 countries worldwide. Oxbow is a world leader in the production and distribution of calcined petroleum coke and the distribution of fuel grade petroleum coke. Oxbow also provides bulk storage and handling for petroleum coke and other commodities. Oxbow‚Äôs scale, expertise and leading market positions have allowed it to create a powerful global sourcing platform with superior market intelligence and longstanding relationships with many of its key suppliers and customers. Oxbow‚Äôs products are essential in the production of aluminum, steel, glass and cement and our specialty products are used in variety of innovative products, including high performance plastics, solar panels, electronics and batteries.

resumen:
Tiger Offshore Rentals a leading global provider of specialty rental equipment to the upstream offshore oil and gas market. We provide DNV 2.7-1 offshore CCU's, and other equipment, from bases in North & South America, East & South Africa, the Mediterranean, and the Middle East. 

We serve offshore E&P operators, drilling contractors, pipe laying vessels and any party needing to transport goods, fluids, tools, dry bulk, or groceries offshore safely. Some categories of equipment we provide are:

- Offshore cargo-carrying equipment
- Offshore cargo boxes and baskets
- Offshore refrigerated containers
- Closed mud skips / cuttings boxes for drilling waste
- Dry goods containers for the offshore industry
- Fluid transport tanks
- ECOmats
- Pressure washers
- Pumps

Our equipment complies with the following standards: DNV 2.7-1, DNV 2.7-3, EN12079, IMDG (T-11) ASME VIII, IBC, IM101, MPT, ISO, UN31H2/HM-181E, UN31A, and are designed for offshore lifting in accordance with API RP 2A.
